b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Bardeen is best suited for sales teams, recruiters, individual professionals, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Relay.app, meanwhile, shines for teams needing approval flows, operations, customer success, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, Bardeen describes itself as \"AI-powered browser automation that runs in your Chrome tab.\" Relay.app, established in 2021, positions itself as \"Automation platform with human-in-the-loop approval workflows.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Relay.app** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 6), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Bardeen is a poor choice — far from it. Bardeen excels in its own right, particularly for sales teams and recruiters.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value unique human-in-the-loop approach, go with Relay.app. If runs directly in browser—no server needed matters more to you, Bardeen is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
